725497f-a.title: Queens: 58th Street - Woodside Avenue
725497f-a.text:
58th Street, east side, north from Woodside Avenue, showing
a group of old mansions. YThe thoroughfare was formely called
Fifth Street.
P. L. Sperr  October 27, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725496f-a.title: Queens: 58th Street - Woodside Avenue
725496f-a.text:
58th Street, east side, between Woodside and 39th Avenues,
showing the mansion which was owned by N.Terret in 1891. 58th
Streot, here, was then named Fifth Street.
P. L. Sperr  October 27, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS

728230f-a.title: Queens: Woodside Avenue - 58th Street
728230f-a.text:
58-07 Woodside Avenue, north side, between 58th and
59th Streets, showing an old home, about 175 feet back of
the normal building line.
P. L. Sperr  November 5, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS
